## 3. AI Engine — MiniGPT Virtual Scout

### 3.1 Architecture Overview

MiniGPT is a **decoder-only causal Transformer** built from scratch following the [Sebastian Raschka "LLMs from Scratch" methodology](https://github.com/rasbt/LLMs-from-scratch). It is **not** a fine-tuned GPT or BERT derivative — every layer, attention head, and embedding is purpose-built for athletic performance analysis.

```mermaid
graph LR
    subgraph Input
        A["Metric String<br/>'SPEED:075 STRENGTH:082...'"]
    end
    subgraph Tokenizer
        B["AthleteTokenizer<br/>Character-level encode"]
    end
    subgraph Transformer["MiniGPT (4 Blocks)"]
        C["Token Embedding<br/>vocab → 128-dim"]
        D["Positional Embedding<br/>pos → 128-dim"]
        E["4× Transformer Block<br/>Pre-LN → Attention → MLP"]
        F["Final LayerNorm"]
    end
    subgraph Output
        G["Mean Pool<br/>(B,T,128) → (B,128)"]
        H["Segment Extraction<br/>4 × 32-dim signals"]
        I["Scout Narrative<br/>Template Selection"]
    end

    A --> B --> C
    C --> E
    D --> E
    E --> F --> G --> H --> I
```

### 3.2 Model Configuration

```python
@dataclass
class GPTConfig:
    block_size: int = 64      # Maximum sequence length (tokens)
    vocab_size: int = 44      # Set by AthleteTokenizer (4 special + 40 chars)
    n_layer: int = 4          # Transformer blocks
    n_head: int = 4           # Attention heads per block
    n_embd: int = 128         # Embedding / hidden dimension
    dropout: float = 0.1      # Dropout probability
```

| Parameter | Value | Rationale |
|---|---|---|
| **Layers** | 4 | Sufficient depth for metric pattern recognition without overfitting on small sequences |
| **Heads** | 4 | Each head can specialise on one metric dimension (speed/strength/stamina/tactical) |
| **Embedding Dim** | 128 | 4 heads × 32 dim/head — compact but expressive |
| **Block Size** | 64 | Fits ~2-3 full metric records after tokenization |
| **Dropout** | 0.1 | Light regularization for inference stability |
| **Total Parameters** | ~530K | Lightweight enough for CPU inference in <50ms |

### 3.3 Transformer Block Architecture

Each of the 4 blocks follows the **Pre-LayerNorm** residual pattern (GPT-2 style):

```
x = x + CausalSelfAttention(LayerNorm(x))
x = x + MLP(LayerNorm(x))
```

#### Causal Self-Attention
- **Combined QKV projection**: Single `nn.Linear(128, 384)` split into Q, K, V
- **Scaled dot-product**: `att = (Q @ K^T) / sqrt(head_dim)`
- **Causal mask**: Lower-triangular matrix prevents future token attention
- **Dropout on attention weights**: 10% during training

#### Feed-Forward Network (MLP)
- **Expansion factor**: 4× (128 → 512 → 128)
- **Activation**: GeLU (Gaussian Error Linear Unit)
- **Architecture**: `Linear(128,512) → GeLU → Linear(512,128) → Dropout`

### 3.4 AthleteTokenizer — Character-Level Encoding

Unlike GPT's BPE (Byte Pair Encoding) or BERT's WordPiece, Proplay uses a **custom character-level tokenizer** specifically designed for structured metric data.

#### Vocabulary (44 tokens)

| Token Type | Tokens | IDs |
|---|---|---|
| Special | `[PAD]`, `[START]`, `[END]`, `[SEP]` | 0–3 |
| Digits | `0-9` | 4–13 |
| Letters | `A-Z` | 14–39 |
| Punctuation | `:`, ` `, `\|`, `.` | 40–43 |

#### Input Format

```
[START] SPEED:075 STRENGTH:082 STAMINA:068 TACTICAL:071 | SPEED:080 ... [END] [PAD]...
```

Each metric record is formatted as `METRIC:NNN` (zero-padded to 3 digits), records separated by ` | `, padded/truncated to exactly 64 tokens.

#### Why Character-Level over BPE?

| Aspect | BPE (GPT-style) | Character-Level (Proplay) |
|---|---|---|
| **Vocabulary** | 50,000+ tokens | 44 tokens |
| **Metric precision** | Numbers tokenized inconsistently | Every digit is a distinct token |
| **Training data needed** | Millions of examples | Works with small datasets |
| **Overhead** | Large embedding table | Tiny embedding table (44 × 128) |
| **Domain fit** | General text | Purpose-built for `METRIC:VALUE` format |

### 3.5 Scout Report Generation Pipeline

The full pipeline from raw metrics to professional narrative:

```
Step 1: Format metrics → "SPEED:075 STRENGTH:082 STAMINA:068 TACTICAL:071"
Step 2: Tokenize → [1, 24, 21, 14, 14, 13, 40, 4, 7, 5, ...]  (64 tokens)
Step 3: Forward pass → 4-layer transformer produces hidden states (1, 64, 128)
Step 4: Mean-pool → single 128-dim vector representing the performance trajectory
Step 5: Extract signals → split into 4 segments of 32 dims, each representing one metric
Step 6: tanh-scale → normalize signals to [-3, +3] bias range
Step 7: Adjust scores → raw_avg + transformer_bias = adjusted score
Step 8: Template selection → choose narrative templates based on adjusted score tiers
Step 9: Assemble report → structured scout assessment with classification
```

The transformer's hidden state doesn't just pass through — it **genuinely influences** the final narrative by biasing the adjusted scores, meaning the same raw metrics can produce different reports depending on the temporal patterns in the training sequence.

### 3.6 Scoring System

#### Sport-Specific Composite Weights

| Sport | Speed | Strength | Stamina | Tactical |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| **Cricket** | 0.20 | 0.30 | 0.20 | 0.30 |
| **Basketball** | 0.30 | 0.20 | 0.30 | 0.20 |
| **Default** | 0.25 | 0.25 | 0.25 | 0.25 |

#### Classification Tiers

| Composite Score | Classification | Action |
|---|---|---|
| ≥ 85 | **ELITE PROSPECT** | Immediate senior scouting review |
| 70–84 | **HIGH POTENTIAL** | Targeted coaching investment |
| 55–69 | **DEVELOPING TALENT** | 6–12 month structured development |
| < 55 | **EARLY STAGE** | Foundational conditioning programmes |

### 3.7 Growth Prediction

Uses **scikit-learn LinearRegression** on historical session scores:

```python
X = [0, 1, 2, 3, ...]    # Time steps
y = [65, 68, 72, 71, ...]  # Session averages

model.fit(X, y)
velocity = model.coef_[0]  # Improvement rate (pts/session)
predicted_next = model.predict([[next_step]])
```

| Velocity | Interpretation |
|---|---|
| > +2.0 | High-velocity growth — accelerated pathway |
| +0.5 to +2.0 | Steady growth — current programme effective |
| 0 to +0.5 | Plateau — programme refresh needed |
| < 0 | Declining — immediate coach review |

