## 9. Comparison with Traditional Methods

### 9.1 Traditional Scouting vs Proplay

| Dimension | Traditional Scouting | Proplay |
|---|---|---|
| **Evaluation method** | Subjective observation by human scouts | Quantitative composite scores with sport-specific weights |
| **Bias** | Personal preferences, recency bias, reputation bias | Algorithmic — same metrics always produce same scores |
| **Speed** | Weeks to months per evaluation | Real-time scoring on metric submission |
| **Scalability** | 1 scout ≈ 10-20 athletes/month | 1 server ≈ unlimited concurrent evaluations |
| **Narrative reports** | Hand-written, inconsistent format | MiniGPT generates structured professional narratives |
| **Growth tracking** | Intuition-based | Linear regression with quantified improvement velocity |
| **Data integrity** | Trust-based, no audit trail | SHA-256 hashed, blockchain-verified |
| **Cost per evaluation** | $500-5,000 (scout travel + time) | ~$0 (compute cost) |
| **Accessibility** | Only elite-level athletes get scouted | Any athlete with metrics can get a scout report |

### 9.2 Traditional Stats Platforms vs Proplay

| Feature | ESPN/Cricbuzz/etc. | Proplay |
|---|---|---|
| **Target audience** | Professional leagues | Grassroots + amateur athletes |
| **Analytics depth** | Surface stats (runs, goals, points) | Multi-dimensional (speed, strength, stamina, tactical) |
| **AI narrative** | ❌ None | ✅ Transformer-generated scout reports |
| **Growth prediction** | ❌ None | ✅ Linear regression velocity tracking |
| **Blockchain verification** | ❌ None | ✅ On-chain proof of performance |
| **Academy management** | ❌ None | ✅ Full creation + discovery system |
| **Direct messaging** | ❌ None | ✅ Athlete-Scout-Coach messaging |
| **Event discovery** | Partial (schedules) | ✅ Open matches + creation + sport filters |

### 9.3 Traditional Web2 vs Web3 Integration

| Approach | Web2-Only (traditional) | Proplay (Web2 + Web3) |
|---|---|---|
| **Data storage** | Centralized database only | Database + on-chain hash verification |
| **Tampering risk** | Database admin can modify records | Hash mismatch immediately detected |
| **Trust model** | "Trust the platform" | "Verify on-chain" (trustless) |
| **Audit trail** | Internal logs (can be deleted) | Immutable blockchain events |
| **Scout confidence** | Must trust data source | Can independently verify via PolygonScan |

